    <exercise id="fs-id1592552" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2695156">    <para id="import-auto-id1168465429824">Nuclear fusion, the energy source of the Sun, hydrogen bombs, and fusion reactors, occurs much more readily when the average kinetic energy of the atoms is high—that is, at high temperatures. Suppose you want the atoms in your fusion experiment to have average kinetic energies of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>40</m:mtext><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo><m:mtext>14</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>J</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>. What temperature is needed?</para></problem></exercise>
    <exercise id="fs-id1616491" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2278262">    <para id="import-auto-id1168465429870">Suppose that the average velocity <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>rms</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> of carbon dioxide molecules (molecular mass is equal to 44.0 g/mol) in a flame is found to be <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>05</m:mtext><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>. What temperature does this represent?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1609625">
    <para id="eip-id2650270"><m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mtext>95</m:mtext>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mtext>10</m:mtext>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:msup>
