    <exercise id="fs-id2720605" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id952848">    <para id="import-auto-id1168465430034">Much of the gas near the Sun is atomic hydrogen. Its temperature would have to be <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>K</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> for the average velocity <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>rms</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> to equal the escape velocity from the Sun. What is that velocity?</para></problem>
